==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neo-Malthusian
<hw>Ne`o-Mal*thu"sian</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Designating, or
pertaining to, a group of modern economists who hold to the
Malthusianism doctrine that permanent betterment of the general standard
of living is impossible without decrease of competition by limitation of
the number of births.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ne`o-Mal*thu"sian</wf>,
<wf>Ne`o-Mal*thu"sian*ism</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neomenia</ent>⟦br⟧
